This paper is primarily focused on multi-robot motion planning, which is a subfield of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the use of heuristics and optimization techniques to improve the efficiency and quality of the planning process, which are common topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.MA). The paper also discusses the use of theoretical analysis to identify conditions for convergence to optimal paths, which is related to control theory (cs.SY). Finally, the paper presents experimental results to demonstrate the effectiveness of the proposed algorithm, which is a common practice in machine learning (cs.LG).
